Math

useful Math methods

Math.round() = rounds a floating point number to a whole number
Math.ceil() = returns the smallest integer that is greater than or equal to the argument passed in, e.g 1.1 becomes 2.
Math.floor() = returns the largest integer that is smaller than or equal to the argument passed in, e.g 1.1 becomes 1.
Math.max() = returns the greater of two values.
Math.min() = returns the lesser of two values.
math.random() = generates a random number between 0 and 1.
Math.pow() = returns the value of a base raised to a power.